<section class="mt-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Real Quick – What Is A Right Triangle?</h2>

  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Before we jump in, let's make sure we're on the same page.
  </p>

  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    A right triangle is just a triangle with one 90-degree angle. That's it.
  </p>

  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The sides have names. The longest one is the <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">hypotenuse</span>. It's always across from the 90-degree corner. The two shorter ones are <span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">legs</span>. They meet at the right angle.
  </p>

  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    That's all you need to know about the hypotenuse and legs to get started.
  </p>
</section>

